Melody Sachs says Jonathan Ross should have been sacked for insulting her husband Melody Sachs, wife of Andrew Sachs, said Jonathan Ross should have been sacked for his role in leaving lewd voice messages on her husband's mobile telephone. Melody Sachs, wife of actor Andrew Sachs who had abusive messages left on his answerphone by Jonathan Ross and Russell Brand during a show recorded for BBC Radio 2. Photo: PA	By Graham Tibbetts 8:16AM GMT 29 Nov 2008
Mrs Sachs, 75, spoke for the first time about the scandal in which Ross claimed on Radio 2 that Russell Brand had slept with the Sachses' granddaughter, Georgina Baillie.She had been in hospital for an emergency hip replacement operation when the extent of the messages - and the public outrage to them - became clear last month."When I first heard the broadcast, I couldn't believe what I was hearing - the repeated abuse of my husband coming from the mouths of two grown men. How low can they get? It was very, very upsetting," she told the Daily Mail."Andrew is a wonderful man and the last person in the world to deserve their ridicule. Seeing all these images on screen of him walking out of our house alone in his little woolly hat being pursued by the Press, I felt so sad for him."Brand, who hosted the radio show in question, has since resigned.
Related Articles
